        lesson 4

        FOLDER STRUCTURE

              1       tsconfig.json
                       - basic typescript settings

            2       src
                      -app module
                          -app component 
                              -app.component.html   -> html code
                              -app.component.scss   -> style sheet
                              -app.component.spec.ts  -> unit test script
                              - app.component.ts  -> class file
               

               3)  assets
                     -images
                     -mock data
                     -apis


                4)  environments

                     -dev
                     -local
                     -prodection

                     

                 5) index.html
                       single page application
                         
                         dynamicaly data get injected into index.html

                         <app-root>  - code injected at run time




                  6)   main.ts

                        --bootstrap module -- it means when application starts it will see main.ts which module to boot

                              
                              -- appModule

                              -- starting point of your application


                               -- default appmodule will start
                                
                                -- we can also can change the module when necessory

                                --No mandatory it should be in appmodule we can change it





                         7) polyfills.ts

                               --  supporting older browsers


                          8) styles.css
                                --global stylesheet for global





                          9) test.ts

                             --test scripts for the main.ts file
                             
                             --tesing the main.ts file code

                               

                     10  angular.js
                          --backbone of the application
                             
                             --scripts
                             -->ports
                             --> settings

                             --schematics
                                  -->build
                                  -->test


                          11 karma.conf.js

                             -->spec.ts
                             -->  test script runner
                             -->running or executing all our test scripts

                          
                          12   tsconfig   
                              
                              configuation for type Script

                                 ---bulid output directory
                                 --sourcemap
                                 --using while deployment

                          13 tslint
                              --recommandation
                              --waring
                              --spacing
                              --enforce coding standards


      lesson 5
           BOOTING PROCESS IN ANGULAR

            to start application === ng serve command

               --compiling the app
                   -- go to main.ts to bootstrap module
                          it will go to module located in main.ts if it is app module it go to app module

                           -- app module 
                                 --app component

                                 if mains.ts contains other component it will go it for expample
                                     
                                     --AuthModule
                                         loginCompount
                                         homeComponent

                                         if we use other module we should go test.ts file and change the component name

              --- whenever we do a ng serve/build/test

              compile your typescript int javascript code into es6 featuers
                  --transpiling
                  --it will generate 
                    1) main.js
                    2) polyfills.js
                    3) main.js.map
                    4) runtime.js


                        



                                 





                          






   